Melt butter in large saucepan; cook onion and mushrooms until tender. Stir in flour. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in chicken broth and cooking wine. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil; boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in wild rice, ham and carrots; simmer 5 minutes. Stir in half-and-half; cook until thoroughly heated. Do not boil. Garnish with parsley.